Telkom is in agreement with the Competition Commission’s final findings on its data market inquiry, that MTN and Vodacom dominate South Africa’s market. Telkom’s obligations are different to that of MTN and Vodacom as they have 3 months to engage with the commission to discuss fixed line roaming and national roaming infrastructure adjustments. Joining CNBC Africa to unpack more is Siyabonga Mahlangu, Group Executive of Regulatory Affairs at Telkom.